  <metadata>
    <name>Gorges of Poëta-Raisse</name>
    <desc>Not far from the charming village of Môtiers and its Absinthe House, the Rousseau waterfall and its eponymous cave mark the beginning of a hike full of contrasts. This is where the gorge trail begins, through a series of ravines and waterfalls. A setting worthy of the land of absinthe, from which a fairy could well emerge... A green alpine landscape follows on the descent to Fleurier.</desc>
    <time>2026-04-28T18:38:43+02:00</time>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/841946/1/desti-vdt-lr-1c0a3830-valentine-jequier_800.jpg">
        <text>Poëta-Raisse-Schluchten (Valentine Jequier)</text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/76556/1/gorges-poeta-raisse-gou-et-et-re-uegion-1_800.JPG">
        <text>Gorges de la Poeta Raisse </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/76554/1/gorges-poeta-raisse-gou-et-et-re-uegion-8_800.JPG">
        <text>Gorges de la Poeta Raisse </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/204458/1/gorges-de-la-poeta-raisse_800.jpg">
        <text>Poëta-Raisse Schluchten (Tourisme neuchâtelois)</text>
    </link>
      </metadata>

    <wpt lat="46.910061150014" lon="6.6116559505463">
        <ele>739.44683837891</ele>
      
    <name>Absinthe House</name>
    <desc>An interpretation centre in the heart of the Val-de-Travers, the Absinthe House tells the story of a drink born here, from its botanical origins and tasting rituals to its clandestine period and its role in local life.
Through a contemporary exhibition route, the visit highlights the plants, expertise and practices that have shaped absinthe, before naturally extending into a tasting or a convivial moment at the bar. In fine weather, the terrace at the rear of the building offers a peaceful setting, surrounded by the emblematic absinthe plants—an ideal place to enjoy a quiet moment.
The experience can then continue in the shop, which offers a selection of exceptional absinthes as well as related products, allowing visitors to take home a unique souvenir from the Val-de-Travers.</desc>
    
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64111/1/mabs-matin_800.jpg">
        <text>Absinth-Haus </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64112/1/mda-interieur-19_800.jpg">
        <text>Absinth-Haus </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64113/1/mda-interieur-03_800.jpg">
        <text>Absinth-Haus </text>
    </link>
      </wpt>
    <wpt lat="46.8862903" lon="6.5511509">
        <ele>778.60949707031</ele>
      
    <name>Cross-country scooters</name>
    <desc>Forget the urban scooter: at La Robella, it turns into a true adventure ride! After a relaxing chairlift ascent, set off on a thrilling descent of several kilometres along one of the three marked trails linking the summit to the village of Buttes. Black run (difficult), red run (intermediate) or blue run (easy) — there’s something for every skill level.</desc>
    
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64058/1/rob-trot-xl-08-18-3526_800.jpg">
        <text>Mountain-trottinets </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64064/1/rob-trot-08-18-3717_800.jpg">
        <text>Mountain-trottinets </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64055/1/rob-trot-xl-08-18-3516_800.jpg">
        <text>Mountain-trottinets </text>
    </link>
      </wpt>
  
